positive.review:
[h1] XCOM: Fantasy Unknown[/h1]
For me this game became a surprise, to be sure, but a welcome one! 
Main goal of qualitative game design is to provide proper experience to player, and this game does this 100% well. Most of things you imagine guild master and adventurers does — you’ll go through in this game, and all ingame systems synergize pretty well. Most important is: you’re enjoying process of playing it, bcs every time this game knows how to pleasantly surprise you.

[h2] Gameplay of "Our Adventurer Guild" contains 3 layers: [/h2]
[olist]
    [*][b] Hub[/b]. There you can talk with staff of the adventurer guild (works same as Normandia in ME, camp in DA or BG3, Ebon Hawk in Kotor etc). You can hire adventurers, edit their appearance, level up them, create own builds of adventurers and their party, solve their problems and do things that improves their relationships. You can ask blacksmith to create equipment, alchemist to make potions and priest to heal your party with their very painful magic. Also, every ingame day there is a chance of random generated events to happen. 
After you done all your staff, you pick party of adventurers (4-6 people) and choose adventure mission from list. After doing that you’re going on next layer;  
    [*][b] Adventure map[/b]. Maps are procedurally generated and has different bioms and goals to finish mission (for example: pick up 6 volcanic ores, explore 80% of map, defeat boss dragon etc). On adventure map you can find resources, fight hostile armies, manage the camp when your party needs rest, explore randomly generated events that can make huge impact even outside current adventure etc. When your adventurers meet hostile army, you’re going on the next layer;
    [*][b] Tactical arena[/b]. It works like in “Heroes of might and magic”, but with altitude levels, bushes that can hide your adventurers and other interactive objects. There are a huge variations to make different builds of same classes, for example: Your priest can be focused on heal, or on buffs, or on damaging undead and demons. You’ll don’t have enough skill points to chose all skills, so you must choose what you want and try different builds on different adventurers and try to combine party you’ll enjoy to play the most. Also, all your characters are mortal in battles, so try to do all possible for them to survive.
[/olist]
[h2] Strong sides of the game: [/h2]
[list]
    [*] Variations of builds. You can create awesome synergize between your adventurers squad;
    [*] Tactic battles. It creates tension bcs cost of mistake is your adventurer live, but at same time mesmerizing possibilities in combining skills of your adventurers;
    [*] Quality of text. At first glance it looks pretty simple, but story is really interesting. Great balance of drama and humor. Characters and their motivation are believable, conflicts written pretty well, and storylines (main story line and side stories) are interesting to watch and enjoyable to play;
    [*] Game Desing of big story battles is great, especially the final mission;
    [*] Random generated events are made really well;
[/list]
[h2] Things I really want to see in sequel/DLC: [/h2]
[list]
    [*] Possibility to hire adventurers from different fantasy races (elfes, dwarfs, drows etc, not human only) will be fine addition;
    [*] More classes and types of weapons (dual swords, hummers, maces etc);
    [*] QoL thing: Pls, add function to go back in dialogues (like it is done in most of Visual Novels) to have posstibility to read part of diague you missed by missclick; Accidentally skipped few dialogs so I really felt iack of this function;
    [*] Pls, make bind “create camp” [N] on other button. I missclicked with map [M] I guess hundreds of time;
    [*] Make more conventional options for NG+ (for example: possibility to choose number of points for new characters’ traits, make higher chances for characters to be in romantic relationshinps etc). I know, some of this options you can fix via hex editor, but possibility to do it via in game options is something game really needs;
    [*]Third slot for artifact, that unlocks for adventurer on 12-16 levels. In early game it can break balance too much, but it’s must have in late game for completing desired builds; 
    [*]Fast results of battle with possibility to replay in late game will be fine addition. It's better than trying to elude battles only bcs you’re gone on adventure to find ore for star sword sidequest, and don’t to waste time on filler battles with 12 ghosts.
[/list]

Still, if I understood correctly — game was done only by single person. If so — impressive job! I enjoyed this game a lot! Good luck in future projects!
